commit 6175936bfa96f5a7cdbc18b5e3b1040649b8e223
Author: Bernhard Rosenkränzer <bero@lindev.ch>
Date:   Sun Jul 5 21:22:28 2026 +0200

    Add GIT binary patch output using zlib-ng compression.
    
    Emit reversible Git-format binary diffs (literal/delta, base85, index
    OIDs) instead of a one-line message, so patches can be applied with
    git apply. Compress payloads with zlib-ng and keep --no-binary-patch
    for the classic summary.

diff --git a/NEWS b/NEWS
index 0beca64..081ab4f 100644
--- a/NEWS
+++ b/NEWS
@@ -1,5 +1,17 @@
 GNU diffutils NEWS                                    -*- outline -*-
 
+* Noteworthy changes in release 3.13 (2026-07-05) [stable]
+
+** New features
+
+  diff now emits reversible "GIT binary patch" output when binary files
+  differ, using Git's literal/delta format with base85 encoding.  Payload
+  compression uses zlib-ng.  Use --no-binary-patch to restore the classic
+  one-line "Binary files ... differ" message.  --brief (-q) still reports
+  only that files differ.  Binary patches are omitted for output styles
+  that cannot represent them (ed, RCS, ifdef, side-by-side).
+
+
 * Noteworthy changes in release 3.12 (2025-04-08) [stable]
 
 ** Bug fixes
